# Catalyst One — Enterprise Design & UX Standard v1.0

**Status:** FOUNDATION STANDARD  
**This is not a feature.** It is a permanent design standard for every screen, dashboard, module, workspace, and future development in Catalyst One.

All future implementations **must** comply.

---

## Objective

Catalyst One is an **Enterprise Operating System**.

Every screen must prioritise:

- Usability
- Productivity
- Operational efficiency
- Readability
- Performance
- Enterprise-grade appearance

Never optimise for fitting components. Always optimise for **user workflow**.

---

## The Five Second Rule

A first-time user should understand the purpose of the page within **five seconds**.

The primary action and operational information should be immediately obvious.

---

## Business First Principle

Business data is always more important than decoration.

Dashboards exist to help users **make decisions**, not merely display charts.

Always prioritise operational visibility over visual effects.

---

## Information Hierarchy

Every operational page should follow this priority:

1. Operational Summary
2. Operational Intelligence
3. Business Actions
4. Business Data (Kanban / Tables / Lists)

Business data should remain visible whenever practical.

---

## Viewport Rule

Design primarily for:

- 14-inch laptop
- 15.6-inch laptop
- Desktop monitor

Important operational information should remain visible without unnecessary scrolling.

---

## Above the Fold Rule

Whenever practical, the user should immediately see:

- Dashboard
- Radar / Charts
- **And** at least the beginning of the operational table or Kanban

Operational data must not disappear below the viewport because of oversized components.

---

## Responsive Layout

- Use available screen space intelligently
- Avoid excessive vertical stacking
- Avoid large unused whitespace
- Allow components to resize dynamically
- Avoid fixed heights whenever possible

---

## Filters

- Use compact enterprise filter chips
- Avoid oversized buttons
- Reduce unnecessary padding
- Keep filters on a single compact row whenever practical

---

## Tables

Operational tables are **primary business tools**.

Never sacrifice table visibility for decorative widgets.

If space is limited, **reorganise the layout** instead of pushing the table downward.

---

## Charts

- Charts may resize dynamically
- Labels must never overlap charts
- Maintain comfortable spacing
- Increase chart size if required to preserve readability

---

## CHANAKYA Radar

The Radar is a live operational intelligence component.

- Quadrant labels must remain **outside** the radar boundary
- Labels must never overlap the radar
- Radar should automatically resize if necessary
- Hover interactions should remain unobstructed

---

## Cards

- Consistent spacing
- Avoid oversized cards and excessive padding
- Display meaningful information only

---

## Scrolling

- Every page must remain scrollable when content exceeds the viewport
- No operational information may become inaccessible
- Avoid nested scrolling unless absolutely necessary

---

## Consistency

Maintain consistent spacing, padding, alignment, typography, button heights, corner radius, animation behaviour, and colour usage throughout Catalyst One.

---

## Performance

No visual enhancement should reduce responsiveness.

Every new feature should:

- Support lazy loading where applicable
- Minimise unnecessary rendering
- Avoid unnecessary database / storage calls
- Maintain fast dashboard performance

---

## UX Validation (Definition of Done)

Before marking any screen complete, confirm:

- No overlapping elements
- No clipped content
- Proper page scrolling
- Business data remains visible
- Charts are readable
- Tables are accessible
- Responsive across common screen sizes
- Visual balance maintained
- Enterprise appearance maintained

If **any** answer is NO, the implementation is **not** production-ready.

---

## Final Principle

When visual design conflicts with business usability, **always choose business usability**.

Catalyst One is an Enterprise Operating System. **Productivity always takes priority over decoration.**

---

## Relationship to other rules

- Complements `enterprise-workspace-ux.mdc` (workspace chrome, Close, document scroll).
- Complements `enterprise-accessibility-contrast.mdc` (contrast).
- Complements `chanakya-radar.mdc` (Radar module specifics).
- When rules overlap, satisfy **this foundation standard** and the more specific module rule.
